GOVERNORSHIP aspirant on the platform of All Progressives Congress (APC) in Kebbi State, Salihu Nataro, has lost his father, Pa Alhaji Isa.
 
Pa Isa, who passed on Monday, was buried same day according to Islamic rites. He reportedly sacrificed all his life building school blocks for both Western and Islamic education, and gave many pupils scholarship.
 
Dignitaries, who witnessed his burial, include Kebbi State Governor, Abubakar Bagudu; former military governor of Kaduna State, Col. Dangiwa Umar (rtd); former Supreme Court Judge, Justice Uthman Mohammed and Mr. Ahmed Umar.